$ SQLcl: SET PARAMETERPOLICY
@ parameterpolicy

code {
set parameterpolicy [share | isolate]
code }

The default value of `parameterpolicy` is `share`. In this mode, arguments (but *not* → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/_variables[variables]!) are global.
-
By setting the value to `isolate`, an SQL script creates a private copy of the values of the arguments. This copy is discarded when the script exits.

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQLcl/commands/set`

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQLcl/commands/argument`

